A man has been arrested on suspicion of murdering a young child found in a critically ill condition.Police officers and paramedics were called to Frosterley Drive, near Haughton Road in Darlington, at 09:00 GMT on Friday morning.The one-year-old was was taken to the Royal Victoria Infirmary in Newcastle but died on Saturday afternoon.A woman in her 40s has been arrested on suspicion of causing or allowing serious injury to a child.
The man, who is in his 30s,  has also been arrested on suspicion of causing or allowing serious injury to a child.Both have been released on conditional bail while further inquiries are carried out, Durham Police said.
